OL,5, In a small community deep in the       
OL,6, remote, lush mountains of Bahia,       
OL,7, Brazil, Catarina Oliveira de Silva     
OL,8, points down at what used to be a lake. 
OL,10,F"After the mine started extracting     
OL,11,Fthere, waste came down. It fell into   
OL,12,Fthe spring. It buried this entire lake.
OL,13,FThree metres of silt and ore sludge."  
OL,15,FCatarina says dust from this mine      
OL,16,Fcovered crops she owned, including     
OL,17,Fcoffee bushes and banana trees, until  
OL,18,Fshe could not produce them anymore.    
